 1640<br>Se Cathedral is considered among the largest church in Goa. This church was built to celebrate the victory of Portuguese ruler Afonso de Albuquerque for capturing a Goan city. St Catherine is worshipped at this church by devotees. This church has Portuguese-Manueline architectural style with a large bell known as Great Golden Bell- which is the largest in the state. <br><br><strong>3)Our Lady of Immaculate Conception<\/strong><br>Location:- Altinho, Panaji, Goa 403001<br>Established:- 1609<br>Our Lady of Immaculate Conception is one of the oldest church in Goa. This church is an example of the \u00a0Baroque architecture with the simple and elegant exterior. It has a double flight of symmetrical stairs with a well-maintained interior. Church has two altars- \u00a0one is dedicated to Our Lady of Rosary and other to St. Peter. The Xavier\u2019s Chapel within the church. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4)St. Cajetan<\/strong><br>Location:- Velha Goa, Goa 403402<br>Established:- 1661<br>Church of St. Cajetan is another wondrous creation on the land of Goa and among the most visited churches by locals and tourist. This church resembles the St. Peter\u2019s Church in Rome. A church depicts the Corinthian style of architecture with the rectangular tower and the beautiful baroque interior. Interior is divided into two sections where each section has an aisle and flanking them are massive pillars. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5)Mae De Deus Church<\/strong><br>Location:- Chogm Rd, Saligao, Goa, 403511<br>Established:- 1873<br>Mae De Deus Church is one of the finest architectural marvels on the Goan Land. This church is one of the most visited churches in Goa by locals as well as tourist, having gothic architecture and ornate interiors. It has a pointed arch, with buttresses supporting its exteriors, belfry, and spikes. Its lighted view in the evenings is at its best. <br><br><strong>6)St Francis of Assisi &nbsp;&nbsp;<\/strong><br> Location:- Off National Highway 4, Velha Goa, Goa 403110<br>Established:- 1661<br>The Church of Saint Francis of Assisi is a Roman Catholic Church and is one of the prime attraction for the travelers. It is a perfect combination of Tuscan, Baroque and Corinthian architecture making it different and unique. The main entrance of the church is built in a Manueline style and exterior have an impression of Tuscan architecture. The interior of the church has a richly ornamental niche. This church also houses a museum established by &nbsp;Archaeological Survey of India in 1964 containing artifacts, paintings and pieces of Hindu temple sculptures from Goa.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Today we are going to give you a list of Top 6 Famous Churches in Goa. Apart from the beaches, crazy nightlife, and fun, the churches in Goa with beautiful architecture and design also hold the key attraction for many travelers who come down to Goa from around the world. Goa houses many small, big [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":531,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/592"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=592"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/592\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":605,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/592\/revisions\/605"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/531"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"htt